<h3>Tips</h3>
<div id="tips" style="margin-left:2em">

<div class="tip">
    <h4>Dictionary for BGFit:</h4>
    <div>
        <dl>
            <dt>Project</dt>
            <dd>A top-level layer where permissions and public scope of the data is defined (see in "Manage data" topic below)</dd>
            <dt>Experiment</dt>
            <dd>Folder that aggregates different collections of data, which can also be modeled</dd>
            <dt>Measurement</dt>
            <dd>3-dimensional data that can also be annotaded. Each measurement can be modeled.</dd>
            <dt>Model</dt>
            <dd>Model extension that is available in BGFIT. This can be a dynamic model that is defined using a diferential or algebraic equation.</dd>
            <dt>Proxy Model</dt>
            <dd>These are implementation of models that are associated with the set of data (either measurement or experiment) that will model this set.</dd>
        </dl>
    </div>

</div>

